I've done this bunches of times without a tool. You
can eyeball it to center by looking dead center
into the hole in the pressure plate, and using a screwdriver
to get it as close as you can, so it's even all
the way 'round.  YOu have a couple millimeters to play 
with, so it's not as critical as say, a crank bearing...

